#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:7
msgid ""
"Idris includes a simple system for building packages from a package "
"description file. These files can be used with the Idris compiler to manage "
"the development process of your Idris programmes and packages."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:13
msgid "Package Descriptions"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:15
msgid "A package description includes the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:17
msgid ""
"A header, consisting of the keyword package followed by the package name."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:18
msgid "Fields describing package contents, ``<field> = <value>``"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:20
msgid ""
"At least one field must be the modules field, where the value is a comma "
"separated list of modules.  For example, a library test which has two "
"modules ``foo.idr`` and ``bar.idr`` as source files would be written as "
"follows::"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:29
msgid ""
"Other examples of package files can be found in the ``libs`` directory of "
"the main Idris repository, and in `third-party libraries <https://github.com"
"/idris-lang/Idris-dev/wiki/Libraries>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:32
msgid "Other common fields which may be present in an ``ipkg`` file are:"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:34
msgid ""
"``sourcedir = <dir>``, which gives the directory (relative to the current "
"directory) which contains the source. Default is the current directory."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:38
msgid ""
"``executable = <output>``, which gives the name of the executable file to "
"generate."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:41
msgid ""
"``main = <module>``, which gives the name of the main module, and must be "
"present if the executable field is present."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:44
msgid ""
"``opts = \"<idris options>\"``, which allows options (such as other "
"packages) to be passed to Idris."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:47
msgid ""
"In more advanced cases, particularly to support creating bindings to "
"external ``C`` libraries, the following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:50
msgid ""
"``makefile = <file>``, which specifies a ``Makefile``, to be built before "
"the Idris modules, for example to support linking with a ``C`` library."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:54
msgid ""
"``libs = <libs>``, which gives a comma separated list of libraries which "
"must be present for the package to be usable."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\tutorial\packages.rst:57
msgid ""
"``objs = <objs>``, which gives a comma separated list of additional object "
"files to be installed, perhaps generated by the ``Makefile``."
msgstr ""

